fake_review: Great food and decor. The cocktails are unique and it's got a great atmosphere. Extensive whiskey selection. The eggs Benedict and the smoked salmon bagel are delicious brunch options.
Great spot in the new Conrad. I would suggest getting here a bit later in the evening. The views are amazing!!

Really good meal here on a Saturday night.  Cocktails were delicious, probably had one or two too many.  Most of the food was fantastic - Carpaccio and Bone Marrow small plates cured my beef cravings, Brussels Sprouts and Chive Biscuit helped soak up the Bourbon.  By far the stand out was the jalapeno Mac and Cheese, we almost ordered a second helping even though we had way too much food.  Entrees were mostly on point, our table had the Bass, Bison, Scallops, and Strip.  Bison was a little cool when it made it to the table, and not as tender as I thought it was going to be.Real stars though were the service, and the drinks.  Our server Dan was fantastic, attentive, and helpful.  We will definitely be asking for him if we go there again.  We ended up getting a round of fancy drinks made with fog, and the roving drink cart bartender was a lot of fun as well.  Definitely a pricey night of food and drinks, but a great experience overall.
I had a great time here with my friends. We step out pretty late and had fun the whole night

First time being here. Nice place for brunch. It's located in the conrad hotel. Nice ambiance when you come in. I loved the Bloody Mary bar and the Irish coffee was good but a tad bit strong. I got the special which was brisket with potatoes, mushrooms, and some other good stuff. The staff was great and super friendly. And their cinnamon rolls were BOMB. I think that it was a pretty dope spot, very nice and prices were reasonable. Good place to get brunch and definitely worth coming to check out!Best part is that I loved the mini hot sauces they give you!! Matter of fact I took one to go because they gave me two :D
Brunch here is great! View of the city, spacious seating w/ great drinks!! Classy crowd.
This restaurant is so cute! Went here to celebrate my gfs bday and the staff was so accommodating. They brought out a special dessert at the end. Big shout out to our server Tom!
Nice place with good view, good food and definitely good drinks. Will definitely go back!
My Husband and I found this place via Yelp when looking for an remarkable taste in Le Boasta. Very good meat!
